    "Moreover, a wide range of student features has been included in the NTHU dataset, such as demographic, academic, and course-specific features, which have been utilized by researchers to develop DL-based predictive models for student performance Lee et al (2021).",
    "• The FutureLearn dataset (https://www.futurelearn.com), a publicly accessible dataset on student performance collected from the FutureLearn platform, which is a UK-based MOOC provider.",
    "The FutureLearn dataset contains data on over 213,000 students enrolled between 2014 and 2016 on a variety of subjects including business, medicine, and computer science.",
    "Researchers have developed DL-based models for predicting student performance based on a number of features, such as demographic, prior and current academic achievement, and course engagement data Duru et al (2021).",
